citations:
    citation-affc-the-prophet-i:
        source: source-affc
        properties:
            locator: "The Prophet"
            text_from_source: "Nine sons had been born from the loins of Quellon Greyjoy, the Lord of the Iron Islands. Harlon, Quenton, and Donel had been born of Lord Quellon's first wife, a woman of the Stonetrees. Balon, Euron, Victarion, Urrigon, and Aeron were the sons of his second, a Sunderly of Saltcliffe. For a third wife Quellon took a girl from the green lands, who gave him a sickly idiot boy named Robin, the brother best forgotten."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "POV: Aeron Greyjoy (Damphair). Chapter title: The Prophet. Aeron is drowning men on Great Wyk when messengers arrive to tell him King Balon is dead — fallen from a bridge at Pyke during a storm. He learns from Gorold Goodbrother's son Gormond and maester Murenmure that Euron Crow's Eye has already arrived at Lordsport and claimed the Seastone Chair. Aeron rides to Pebbleton, where he decides to call a Kingsmoot on Old Wyk. Provides detailed Greyjoy family history: nine sons of Quellon Greyjoy, fate of Urrigon (lost hand to a flying axe; maester failed to save him), Aeron's earlier life as a drunkard and his near-drowning and religious conversion. Key figures introduced: Gorold Goodbrother of Hammerhorn, Maester Murenmure, The Sparr, Steffarion Sparr, Gormond Goodbrother, Gran Goodbrother, Lord Merlyn (Meldred Merlyn) of Pebbleton, Aeron's drowned men including Norjen and Rus."
